Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Roma Tomatoes{2} into ½-inch cubes. Add half the tomatoes to a #medium pan{} and place over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in half the @Orzo Pasta{6%ounce} from package (use the rest as you like). Cook, stirring, for about ~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pour 1 cup water and a large pinch of salt into pan. Bring to a boil, then lower heat to medium. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Remove pan from heat and stir in @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tablespoon}, two thirds of the @Spinach{5%ounce}, and half the @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup}.

> If mixture seems dry while cooking, add more water, ¼ cup at a time, to loosen.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat @Chicken Cutlets{20%ounce} dry with a paper towel; set aside half. Season other half with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}. Add seasoned chicken to pan and cook until cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside. Mix @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, remaining Tuscan Heat Spice, and a big pinch of salt on a #plate{}.

Season remaining chicken with salt and pepper. Brush with 2 TBSP @Sour Cream{6%tablespoon} (1 packet). Dip into panko mixture one piece at a time, coating all over and pressing to adhere. Transfer to another plate. Heat a ¼-inch layer of oil in another large pan over high heat (we used nonstick). Add breaded chicken and cook until crisp and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side, lowering heat if it browns too quickly. Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Season with salt.

Halve @Lemon{1}. In a #small bowl{}, toss half the remaining spinach with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} and a squeeze of lemon. Season with plenty of salt and pepper. Divide breaded chicken and orzotto between plates. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. Scatter dressed spinach over chicken and serve.

== Lunch ==

After dinner, cut seasoned chicken and @Fresh Mozzarella{4%ounce} into small pieces (about ½ inch). Toss both in a #medium bowl{} with remaining tomatoes, a squeeze or two of lemon, and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Keep refrigerated overnight.

In the morning, toss remaining spinach into chicken mixture. Split @Whole Wheat Pitas{2}, then fill each with chicken mixture and pack. Enjoy cold or at room temperature.

> TIP: Pack the pitas separately and fill just before eating for best results.